do you like this old poem of mine sheryl s smile cold clear water down from a mountain stream cold clear water you soak in my dreams cold clear water you splash me with your smile in your cold clear water i can swim for miles and miles and miles yesterday my first monday without a job in a while my wife called to say hi the first thing she asked was what did you write about today as i started to think she said my favorite thing about coming home from work is getting to read what you ve written this poem above is one i wrote for her just before our first date years ago td there are many things that i enjoy about your work your passion your ability to take small moments being at a baseball game setting up a feast are two that come to mind and extrapolate them without being precocious your love of life and your poetic nature that allows you to express it clearly so in answer to your question yes i like this poem perhaps more later work is waiting Hanshan Gary Snyder Shaggy dog story The Amber Spyglass John Berryman Jon Secada William Shakespeare Anglo-Saxon literature Poetry Four Quartets Time Out of Mind Past teachings of Prem Rawat Swami Vivekananda Sport Sheryl Crow Sydney Riot of 1879 E. E. Cummings Thomas M. Disch Ella Wheeler Wilcox Origin belief Current teachings of Prem Rawat Jack Buck John Cage Parsifal Theocritus Federico Garc__a Lorca Dream Job (Season 2) Chicago Cubs The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Baseball Arthur Machen Eli Siegel Tibullus Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Allen Ginsberg Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Ralph Waldo Emerson Captain Thunderbolt Japanese poetry Fernando Pessoa New York Giants Zhuangzi Abraham Cowley Victor Hugo T. S. Eliot William Butler Yeats Mikhail Lermontov Hall & Oates Talbot County, Maryland William Carlos Williams Meaning of life H.D. Happiness C__dmon Social rule Theory of conduct The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy Primary and Secondary Phases Jennifer Lopez Avenu